<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920313-0056</DOCNO><DOCID>920313-0056.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   Greyhound Lines Inc.</HL><DATE>03/13/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BUS</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)CONSUMER andamp; HOUSEHOLD SERVICES (CSV)CONSUMER AND HOUSEHOLD PRODUCTS AND SERVICES (HOU)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)</IN><NS>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   DALLAS -- Greyhound Lines Inc. filed an amendedregistration statement with the Securities and ExchangeCommission to offer $90 million of convertible subordinateddebentures due March 31, 2007. The bus company said thedebentures offering would replace a proposed offering of $60million of convertible exchangeable preferred stock,announced Jan. 22.   A spokeswoman said market conditions appeared &quot;morereceptive&quot; to the increased offering, which will allowGreyhound to retire certain debts and free up funds toreinvest in the business, which emerged from a Chapter 11reorganization on Oct. 31.</LP><TEXT>   Greyhound said net proceeds from the new offering will beused to repay in full the company's $55.7 million securedterm loan, increase insurance deposits and reduce or repay infull a $22.7 million promissory note owed to Dial Corp. Anyremaining net proceeds will be used for general corporatepurposes and may be applied to repay certain other seniordebt or to make capital expenditures, the company said.   The company said that, to complete the offering, it mustmodify its existing credit agreement and obtain consents fromcertain creditors. Smith Barney, Harris Upham andamp; Co. will bethe sole underwriter.</TEXT></DOC>